---
description: Generic Rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Don't be sycophantic
- Always be clear and precise
- Don't use filler words and sentences
- Always say the truth
- Always be fact oriented and data driven
- Avoid else-statements whenever possible

## Running Tool Commands

The application is running in containers

- Always run the commands in the php container
- To start containers run `make up`
- To run commands run `docker compose exec -T <command>`
- To execute tests run `docker compose exec -T php sh -c "export XDEBUG_MODE=off && bin/console cache:clear && bin/phpunit"`
- To execute PHPStan run `docker compose exec -T php sh -c "export XDEBUG_MODE=off && bin/phpstan"`
- To execute PHPCS run `docker compose exec -T php sh -c "export XDEBUG_MODE=off && bin/phpcs"`
- To execute PHPCBF run `docker compose exec -T php sh -c "export XDEBUG_MODE=off && bin/phpcbf"`

## After Making changes

- Before finishing a task you MUST run PHPCBF
- Before finishing a task you MUST run PHPStan, if there are errors fix them
- Before finishing a task you MUST run PHPUnit, if there are errors fix them
